{
  "texts": [
    "Sequence-based similarity search algorithms, such as FASTA and BLAST, are commonly employed to identify homologous templates from the Protein Data Bank (PDB) dataset [50].",
    "Molecular dynamicsProteins were once believed to be static structures, but this view has been challenged and overturned [51].",
    "Molecular dynamics (MD) is a computer simulation technique employed to predict protein movements and conformational changes over time [52].",
    "Initially introduced by Alder and Wainwright [53], MD simulations have evolved from methods based on Newtonian mechanics to more advanced quantum mechanical approaches [54,55].",
    "MD simulations are widely used to study drug-target interactions, capture multiple conformational changes in proteins, calculate ligand-target binding energies, and identify cryptic or allosteric sites [56,57]."
  ]
}